			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Coking coal, also known as metallurgical coal, is a naturally occurring sedimentary rock. It is a specific type of coal that melts and hardens when heated without air, making it suitable for steel making. When heated, coking coal creates coke, a hard, strong, porous material of high carbon content. This coke is a key material for the production of steel. Coking coal is used in the production of coke, a key ingredient in the steelmaking process.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">焦煤又称冶金煤，是一种天然沉积岩。它是一种特殊的煤，在没有空气的情况下加热时会熔化并变硬，因此适用于炼钢。焦煤在加热时会产生焦炭，这是一种坚硬、结实、多孔的高碳材料。这种焦炭是生产钢铁的关键材料。炼焦煤用于生产炼钢过程中的关键原料--焦炭。</common:generalComment>
